  "instructions": [
    "in a large saucepan, combine the chicken stock cube, chicken breast, onion, garlic, pepper flakes, salt, and black pepper. ",
    "add the heavy cream, lemon juice, parsley, and truffle oil. ",
    "heat the mixture over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the soup starts to simmer. ",
    "transfer the saucepan to a bain-marie, and let it cook for 30 minutes, or until the soup has thickened slightly and the flavors have melded together. ",
    "season the soup with additional salt and pepper to taste. ",
    "serve the soup hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired. ",
    "in a separate saucepan, heat the coconut oil over medium heat. ",
    "add the black pepper, and stir to combine. ",
    "cook for 1-2 minutes, or until fragrant. ",
    "stir the peppery oil into the soup, and serve. "
